<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Names-Regan CORRECTIVE   03-21 0090</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Names-Regan, CORRECTIVE,0089</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>Eds: Members who used the fifth item in a0433, PM-Names, sent
March 18 under a New York dateline, are asked to use the following
story.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously March
18 that a book written by former White House chief of staff Donald
T. Regan would be published nine months later than originally
planned.
   The book, being published by Harcourt Brace Jovanovich, will be
issued this May, four months earlier than first planned, not nine
months later, the publishing house reported.
</TEXT>
