<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Baker,190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Baker Gets New Medal After Original Lost in Break-In</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan presented White House Chief
of Staff Howard Baker with a new presidential Medal of Freedom on
Monday after Baker's original was lost during a weekend break-in at
his home in northwest Washington.
   Baker ``is probably the only person who has received two Medals
of Freedom,'' White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater said.
   Baker and his wife, Joy, were sitting in their living room
Saturday evening when an alarm sounded. Baker went downstairs to
his study to fix what he thought would be an alarm sensor fallen
from a window pane.
   Instead, he discovered a burglar stealing expensive camera
equipment and the former Tennessee senator's Medal of Freedom.
   Baker chased the thief upstairs, downstairs and out while his
wife was phoning District police and White House security. The
burglar dropped most of the stolen items while being chased through
the house and fled into the street.
   Police arrested a man later that evening who had some of the
Bakers' camera equipment but not the medal. The man has refused to
identify himself to police.
</TEXT>
