<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0459</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Snow In Great Lakes; Rain In Northwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Scattered snow fell in the lower Great Lakes region and along
the mid-Atlantic Coast today, while a cold front brought rain to
the Pacific Northwest.
   The Southwest had temperatures in the 50s and 60s early today,
following readings in the 80s and 90s on Sunday in California and
southern Arizona. Yuma, Ariz., had the nation's high Sunday with 95
degrees.
   The heaviest snow today was in the lower Great Lakes region due
to squalls near shore. Forecasters posted lake snow advisories in
New York state along the shore of Lake Ontario, where up to 5
inches was possible.
   In the Pacific Northwest, heavier rainfall totals for the
six-hour period ending at 1 a.m. EST included about a quarter of an
inch at Hoquiam and Fort Lewis, Wash.
   Skies were partly cloudy across much of the northern half of the
nation; clear skies prevailed in the South.
   Today's forecast called for rain scattered across the northern
Plateau and Pacific Northwest; snow scattered across northern areas
of Maine; wind, gusty at times, across the northern third of the
Rockies.
   Highs will be in the 60s or 70s across much of the nation; the
teens and 20s across the northern and eastern areas of the Great
Lakes and northern New England; 30s and 40s from the upper
Mississippi Valley into the northern parts of the lower Ohio Valley
and central Appalachians into southern New England; 50s from the
central Dakotas into the rest of the lower Ohio Valley and
mid-Atlantic states region; 40s and 50s across the Pacific
Northwest and northern Plateau; 80s across the desert Southwest and
across much of Texas, Oklahoma and southwest Kansas; and about 90
over southwest Arizona and southeast California.
   Temperatures around the nation at 2 a.m. EST ranged from 11
below zero at Marquette, Mich., to 67 at Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 51 fair; Boston 16 snow; Buffalo 18 snow;
Charleston, S.C. 50 fair; Cincinnati 30 cloudy; Cleveland 16 fair;
Detroit 20 fair; Miami 53 fair; Philadelphia 27 partly cloudy;
Pittsburgh 20 cloudy; Portland, Maine 11 windy; Washington 33
cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 24 partly cloudy; Chicago 26 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 52 fair; Denver 45 partly cloudy; Des Moines 32
fair; Indianapolis 29 fair; Kansas City 44 fair; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 20 fair; Nashville 56 fair; New Orleans 51 fair; St. Louis 43
fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 43 fair; Anchorage 24 fair; Las Vegas 53
fair; Los Angeles 60 partly cloudy; Phoenix 64 fair; Salt Lake City
49 fair; San Diego 61 partly cloudy; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle
41 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 1 fair; Toronto 16 fair.
</TEXT>
