<HEAD>Bomb Explodes in Beirut; 5 Feared Killed In Tripoli Building
Collapse</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bomb exploded in a four-story apartment
building in Moslem west Beirut today, and police said several
people were believed buried in the rubble.
   The blast occurred at 7 p.m. in the Tarik Jedideh district.
   Civil defense rescue teams and ambulances rushed to the scene,
police said. They had no further details.
   Meanwhile, in Tripoli, 50 miles north of Beirut, an unfinished
eight-story building collapsed at daybreak, burying six
construction workers, police reported.
   They said one worker was rescued after six hours. Although
rescue teams reported hearing moans beneath the wreckage, hopes
were fading at nightfall that any of the others would survive.
   Police said the cause of the building collapse in Tripoli was
not immediately known.
 
