<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Fatal Accident,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Dies After Being Hit By Four Vehicles</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman crossing a street was hit by four
vehicles and killed, police said.
   Janell Bankhead, 25, was hit by a van as she walked across a
street about 12:30 a.m. Sunday. She tried to get up, but a pickup
truck heading in the opposite direction dragged her a short
distance.
   Another van then hit Ms. Bankhead and the driver did not stop.
Then a third van ran over her, police said.
   The drivers who stopped after hitting the woman said they did
not see her in the darkness, police said. Officers were searching
for the driver of the van that did not stop. Drivers of the others
were not cited.
