<DOCNO> AP880321-0181 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-03-21-88 2034EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People SUB a0670 03-21 0219</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People, SUB, a0670,0223</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ed: SUBS PALM SPRINGS, Calif.-dated last item to ADD 2 grafs'
background, that actress undecided about presidential candidate,
convention focused on local races.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALM SPRINGS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former ``Falcon Crest'' siren Morgan
Fairchild is making another name for herself in the muddy waters of
Democratic politics.
   Not content to just raise funds for Democratic causes and
candidates, Ms. Fairchild took on a new role as a delegate at the
state party convention over the weekend.
   ``If you're an actor who has made up your mind about a
presidential candidate, you're asked to go to Iowa, go on national
television and tell everybody why you support the candidate,'' she
said. ``So if you are seriously involved, you have to be willing to
make that commitment and know what you're talking about.''
   But the blond, blue-eyed femme fatale is hardly ready to run for
office herself.
   ``It's the last thing I would think of,'' she said. ``My
contribution right now is in trying to raise funds. People don't
need me to give a speech.''
   Miss Fairchild is undecided on which presidential candidate to
support, said one of her publicists, Rachel Vizcarra. ``She just
hasn't made up her mind yet.''
   During the weekend convention, delegates selected candidates for
backing in local races in the June primary.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
