<TEXT>
   Iranian gunboats attacked and set ablaze
a Spanish freighter and a Liberian tanker in the Persian Gulf on
Monday, two days after an Iraqi attack on a Norweigan vessel left
54 seamen missing and presumed dead.
   There have been six maritime attacks since Friday when Iran, in
apparent reprisal for the resumption of Iraqi strikes against its
oil lifeline, ended a five-week hiatus in assaults on commercial
shipping in the oil-rich waterway.
   There was no word on casualties aboard the 10,168-ton Spanish
