average of 30 industrials edged up 1.33 points to 2,087.37,
stretching its gain for the week to 52.39 points.
   Bond prices dropped in active trading, pressured by resurgent
anxiety about inflation.
   The dollar held its ground against other foreign currencies,
while gold moved higher.
   On other markets, oil futures moved higher for the fourth
consecutive day, wheat was higher while corn and soybeans declined.
