<HEAD>Nestle Appoints Volcker to Board of Directors</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VEVEY, Switzerland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nestle SA, the giant Swiss food
products group, plans to appoint Paul Volcker, former chairman of
the U.S. Federal Reserve, to its board of directors, the company
has announced.
   Shareholders will be asked to elect Volcker and Swiss
industrialist Stephan Schmidheiny to Nestle's board at the
company's general meeting on May 19, the company said Friday.
   Volcker, who last year elected not to accept another term at the
U.S. central bank, earlier this month was named chairman of the New
York investment banking firm James D. Wolfensohn Inc. and as a
professor at Princeton University.
   During his eight years as chairman of the Fed, Volcker gained an
international reputation, which combined with the widespread
connections made during from his tenure as Fed chairman has made
him much sought-after by private business.
