prices in the bond market, a sensitive barometer of inflation and
interest rates. Evidence of economic strength that emerged from
government reports last week suggested that inflation could
intensify, eroding the value of fixed-income investments.
   Among the most prominent losing blue-chips, IBM fell } to 113{,
DuPont fell 1{ to 87\, Philip Morris fell 1] to 92} and Merck fell
1] to 158}.
   Takeover action buoyed some notable issues. Koppers rose 3\ to
57 following another takeover offer of $56 a share from Beazer PLC.
American Standard rose ~ to 76} after Kelso said it would consider
an increase in its $78-a-share offer to thwart counter-offers from
rival Black & Decker.
   On Friday, the Dow Jones industrials managed a 1.33-point
advance to 2,087.37, its second straight post-crash high, but the
broader market was mixed.
